  "summary": "Typosquat of @solana/web3.js exfiltrates host data via postinstall",
  "details": "This package impersonates the legitimate @solana/web3.js library under a confusingly similar scope/name (@solana-labs/web3js). The package.json declares a postinstall hook that runs install.js, which collects host identifiers (hostname references at multiple lines) and exfiltrates them via curl/POST to an external endpoint at install time. Installing this package as a dependency causes automatic outbound transmission of installer machine details on `npm install`, with no relation to any advertised Solana SDK functionality.",
